NewValue - The new value of the mask part.

                The event handler function is called with 2 parameters: 


A reference to the RadMaskedTextBox object which
                    triggered the event;


                        An event arguments object which contains the following properties: 


OldValue - The old value of the mask part;

NewValue - The new value of the mask part.

                The event handler function is called with 2 parameters: 


A reference to the RadMaskedTextBox object that
                    triggered the event;


                        An event arguments object which contains the following properties: 


CurrentPart - A reference to the mask part that triggered the
                            event;

OldValue - The old value of the mask part;

NewValue - The new value of the mask part.

member.example:
    This example demonstrates the usage of the OnClientDown property. 

<script>
function onError(input, args)
{
   alert("Invalid character:" + args.NewValue);
}
</script>

<radI:RadMaskedTextBox
      ID="RadMaskedTextBox1"
      runat="server"
      Mask="<0..255>.<0..255>.<0..255>.<0..255>"
      OnClientError="onError">
</radI:RadMaskedTextBox>

